What is Systems Manager?
Centralized management service for AWS resources.

Key Features:

Session Manager:
Connect to EC2 without SSH.

Patch Manager:
Automate OS updates.

Run Command:
Execute commands remotely.

Inventory:
Collect server information.

Real-Time Scenario:
500 EC2 Instances need patching.

Without SSM:

Login to 500 Servers
Patch Manually

With SSM:

Patch Manager
      ↓
All Servers Updated

Architecture:
Admin
  ↓
SSM
  ↓
EC2 Fleet

Benefits:
Improved Security
Reduced Manual Work
Centralized Management
